65","1450–1489":"1450–1489","1428–Male":"1428–Afdød","1489":"1489","1433":"1433","1465":"1465","1450":"1450","Abt 1428":"omkring 1428","1428":"1428","about 1450":"omkring 1450","Burslem, Staffordshire, England":"Burslem, Staffordshire, England","Oldcott, Wolstanton, Newcastle-under-Lyme district, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Oldcott, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"Abt 1428–":"circa 1428–Overleden","1433–1465":"1433–1465","1450–1489":"1450–1489","1428–Male":"1428–Overleden","1489":"1489","1433":"1433","1465":"1465","1450":"1450","Abt 1428":"circa 1428","1428":"1428","about 1450":"circa 1450","Burslem, Staffordshire, England":"Burslem, Staffordshire, England","Oldcott, Wolstanton, Newcastle-under-Lyme district, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Oldcott, Staffordshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"Abt 1428–":"about 1428–Deceased","1433–1465":"1433–1465","1450–1489":"1450–1489","1428–Male":"1428–Deceased","1489":"1489","1433":"1433","1465":"1465","1450":"1450","Abt 1428":"about 1428","1428":"1428","about 1450":"about 1450","Burslem, Staffordshire, England":"Burslem, Staffordshire, England","Oldcott, Wolstanton, Newcastle-under-Lyme district, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Oldcott, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Rowley","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from one or more of various places called Rowley or Rowly, such as Rowley Regis (Staffordshire), Rowley (Devon, Durham), Rowleygreen Farm (Hertfordshire), Rowly (Surrey), Rowley (East Yorkshire), Rowley, near Bardsey (Yorkshire), Rowley in Lepton (Yorkshire), and Rowley Hill (Essex). The placenames probably all derive from Old English <i>rūh</i> ‘rough’ + <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’, though the East Yorkshire place may have been named with <i>hlāw</i> ‘mound, hill’ as the second element.","Irish: from <b>Ó Roghallaigh</b>, a variant of <b>Ó Raghailligh</b>. See   Riley   and   O'Reilly  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Rowlee","meanings":["English: variant of   Rowley  ."]},{"name":"Roley","meanings":["English: variant of   Rowley  . This surname is now rare in Britain."]},{"name":"Rollie","meanings":["English, Scottish, and Irish: variant of   Rowley  ."]},{"name":"Riley","meanings":["English (Lancashire and Yorkshire): habitational name chiefly from High Ryley in Accrington (Lancashire) and Riley in Kirkburton, which was in the manor of Wakefield (Yorkshire). In some cases the name may derive from Riley Farm in Eyam (Derbyshire), Royley in Royton (Lancashire), or Rylah in Scarcliffe (Derbyshire). The placenames all come from Old English <i>rȳge</i> ‘rye’ + <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’.","Irish: from <b>Ó Raghailligh</b> ‘descendant of <i>Raghailleach</i>’, Old Irish <i>Roghallach</i>. This is the name of a chieftain family in Cavan, related to the O'Rourkes. In Anglicized form it has also been confused with <b>Ó Raithile</b> found in Munster, usually Anglicized as <b>O'Rahilly</b> or   Rahilly  . See   O'Reilly  ."]},{"name":"Rolley","meanings":["English and Irish: variant of   Rowley  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"John Rowley was born about 1428, in Oldcott, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son with Alice Newton."},"et":{"Abt 1428–":"umbes 1428–Surnud","1433–1465":"1433–1465","1450–1489":"1450–1489","1428–Male":"1428–Surnud","1489":"1489","1433":"1433","1465":"1465","1450":"1450","Abt 1428":"umbes 1428","1428":"1428","about 1450":"umbes 1450","Burslem, Staffordshire, England":"Burslem, Staffordshire, England","Oldcott, Wolstanton, Newcastle-under-Lyme district, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Oldcott, Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1428–":"noin 1428–Kuollut","1433–1465":"1433–1465","1450–1489":"1450–1489","1428–M